necessity for those
with serious allergic reactions.

06:06.266 --> 06:11.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Its price has skyrocketed to as
much as $600
for a set of two.

06:11.438 --> 06:16.343 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At first, Mylan offered
financial assistance
to customers, but after mounting
pressure,

06:16.376 --> 06:20.847 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the company said it now will
release a generic
a version for half the price.

06:20.880 --> 06:26.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To give us some perspective on
how this case
is different, Stephen
Schondelmeyer studies

06:26.186 --> 06:30.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this closely at the University
of Minnesota,
and Andrew Pollack covers
pharmaceuticals

06:30.257 --> 06:31.791 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for The New York Times.

06:31.825 --> 06:33.560 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Gentlemen, welcome.

06:33.593 --> 06:36.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Andrew Pollack, I want to start
with you and
ask you to explain just
basically, what's

06:36.263 --> 06:38.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the difference here?

06:38.198 --> 06:42.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's the big deal between a
generic EpiPen
and the kind that this company
has been producing

06:42.102 --> 06:44.170 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and selling at such a markup?

06:44.204 --> 06:48.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW POLLACK, The New York
Times: Well,
it's actually quite a bit
confusing.

06:48.241 --> 06:50.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The products are exactly the
same.

06:50.610 --> 06:51.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's the same product.

06:52.012 --> 06:55.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
However, they are calling one
version now
a generic.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It will have a different package
on it.

06:57.450 --> 07:04.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It won't say EpiPen, and they
will be selling
it for half the list price of
the branded

07:04.124 --> 07:05.091 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
product.

07:05.125 --> 07:06.960 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Has that ever
happened before?

07:06.993 --> 07:12.699 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW POLLACK: Well,
pharmaceutical companies,
brand-name pharmaceutical
companies often

07:12.732 --> 07:19.339 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do introduce their own generic
version of
their own drug.

07:19.372 --> 07:21.741 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's called an authorized
generic.

07:21.775 --> 07:27.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is done once an outside
generic company
comes into the market.

07:27.380 --> 07:34.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This allows them to keep some of
the sales,
rather than having all their
sales being lost

07:34.921 --> 07:36.723 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the outside generic company.

07:36.756 --> 07:44.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is unusual here is that
Mylan doesn't
have an immediate genetic
competitor for the

07:44.130 --> 07:45.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
EpiPen.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So they're basically
competing
against public relations at this
point.

07:47.967 --> 07:54.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Stephen Schondelmeyer, how did a
product that
cost as little as $100 in 2007
rise to $600

07:54.140 --> 07:55.942 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today?

07:55.975 --> 07:59.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STEPHEN SCHONDELMEYER,
University of Minnesota:
Well, it did that because the
marketplace

07:59.612 --> 08:07.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
doesn't have any regulation,
either government
regulation or market regulation,
that holds

08:07.287 --> 08:09.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that down.

08:09.255 --> 08:15.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in fact, this product that
-- at a self-insured
employer I work with, it cost
them $100 for

08:16.029 --> 08:21.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this product in 2011, and today
is costing
them $730.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.970 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That dramatic increase just
isn't seen.

08:24.003 --> 08:26.639 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And now they're calling it a
generic in name.

08:26.673 --> 08:31.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's not a generic, meaning
an independent
economic decision-maker choosing
to compete

08:31.544 --> 08:32.946 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with the price of the brand
name.

08:32.979 --> 08:37.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we won't see this behave like
a normal
generic in the market either.

08:37.450 --> 08:41.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And even if it's
half the price,
it will be still around $300,
which is still

08:41.654 --> 08:44.791 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
more than it was just a short
time ago, right?

08:44.824 --> 08:51.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHEN SCHONDELMEYER: Sure,
it's more than
$200 than it was not too long
ago.

08:51.731 --> 08:56.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is sort of like if your
child happens
to get kidnapped, and the
kidnappers call

08:56.336 --> 09:00.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
